The paper deals with the problem of pattern formation in a distributed system of mobile robots, which is a classic topic in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS) and robotics. The use of probabilistic algorithms and the ASYNC model suggests that the paper is more likely to be classified under the sub-category of "Multiagent Systems" (cs.MA) or "Robotics" (cs.RO). However, the paper also involves the study of deterministic algorithms and the formation of patterns with multiplicity points, which are relevant to the sub-categories of "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC), "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS), and "Systems and Control" (cs.SY).
